title: For Sale/Trade:  COMMERCIAL (Not Sporterized) 98 Mauser For Sale or Trade
postcontent: A German made Suhl Commercial 98 Mauser with no import marks, Suhl lower claw scope mounts (No scope or matching rings unfortunately.), spooned bolt, semi octagonal Krupp barrel and receiver dated originally to 1908 via serial number. She was originally chambered in 8mm Mauser, but rechambered in June of 1929 to 8mm x 60S after WW1 due to The Treaty of Versailles which banned civilians from owning firearms with military chamberings. It was a "liberated" rifle taken from postwar WW2 German.This rifle's seen a lot over the 110 years since it was hand crafted in Germany, as evidenced by it's dinged up beechwood stock, but mechanically the old girl's flawless, she cycles like a brand new Beemer right off the showroom floor. The bore's bright and shiny with very strong lands and grooves and prestine crown.Say what you'd like about Germany itself, but apparently it's true about what's touted of their engineering, because after her bagging of what I'm sure was her fair share of big game back home, two World Wars, and a trip across the Atlantic in one of our servicemens duffle bags, she still hasn't lost her touch.This rifle has tons of history and has seen a LOT over its life, and I'd love to sell or trade her to someone who recognizes and appreciates that. That being said, if I don't feel you'll treat her like the war prize she is, you'll have about as much of a chance of getting her from me as Germany had of winning the war after we decided to join in and save Europes a**.Again, she's a beautifully crafted and balanced rifle with a bit of cosmetic wear to her, but an excellent example of what a hunting rifle should be. I'm open to offers and trades, and the worst I can do is say no.

postcontent: New in box/unused stripped lower from Aero Precision. This is the M4E1 which has a lot of the nice billet features and aesthetics, but has the same pricing as a forged lower. From Aero Precision's website:"The M4E1 Lower Receiver delivers billet aesthetics in a forged package. This custom designed enhanced forging is machined from 7075-T6 Aluminum and compatible with all mil-spec AR15 parts. Aside from the visual upgrades this custom engineered design provides that challenge much more expensive billet options, we have added several functional features to the lower receiver to simplify the assembly process for the at home builder.M4E1 Lower Receiver Improvements:- Threaded Bolt Catch Roll Pin - Allows for simple installation of the bolt catch and virtually eliminates the chance to damage the finish during installation (pin included). 1/16" Hex Key required for assembly.- Integrated Trigger Guard - Eliminates the possibility of breaking the trigger guard tabs by integrating the trigger guard into the lower, creating a stronger more rigid platform to build upon.- Upper Tension Screw - Allows users to fine tune the fit of the upper and lower receiver using a nylon tipped tensioning set screw inserted in the grip tang of the lower receiver. This provides a tight fit with any standard AR15 upper receiver.- Threaded Takedown Pin Detent Recess - Allows user to easily install the Takedown Pin detent and spring with the use of a 4-40 set screw (no more launching detents across the room).- Increased Magwell Flare - Increased the flare of the magwell to aid in quick and efficient magazine changes.- Marked and milled to accept short-throw safety selectors, but will work with standard selectors as well.Includes:- Stripped M4E1 Lower Receiver- Nylon tipped tensioning set screw- Threaded Bolt Catch Pin"https://aeroprecisionusa.com/m4e1-stripped-lower-receiver-fde-cerakote.html$100 cash only, not looking for any trades at the moment.
